âœ… Core Ansible Concepts


Variables

Used to store dynamic values for tasks and playbooks.
Example:
YAML
course:  name: "DevOps with AWS"  duration: 120  trainer: "sivakumar reddy"Show more lines




Conditions (when)

Apply tasks only if certain conditions are met.
Example:
YAMLwhen: ansible_os_family == "RedHat"Show more lines




Loops

Repeat tasks for multiple items.
Example:
YAML
loop:  - item1  - item2
Show more lines




Data Types

YAML supports scalars, lists, and dictionaries.
Example:
YAML- , [][  { "key": "name", "value": "DevOps with AWS" },  { "key": "duration", "value": 120 }]Show more lines



âœ… Functions vs Filters

Ansible doesnâ€™t allow custom functions directly like Python.
To extend functionality, you write Python plugins or use filters.
Filters = used for data manipulation in templates and tasks.

Example:
YAML{{ variable | upper }}Show more lines





âœ… Command vs Shell Modules

command:

Executes simple commands without shell environment.
More secure.


shell:

Executes complex commands (pipes, redirection).
Provides shell environment.


Best Practice: Use command if possible.


âœ… Ansible Beyond Configuration Management

Can connect to any system if a module exists.
Integrates with AWS using aws modules.
Requires AWS CLI setup:
Shellaws configureShow more lines



